    "text": "Our implementation leverages the LangChain framework [ 3 ] for systematic pipeline construction. To mitigate stochastic noise in LLM-generated responses and reduce logical bias, we set the temperature to zero for LLMs. Our approach is implemented in about 8,500 lines of Python code in total. All experiments are conducted on a machine equipped with an AMD EPYC 9654 CPU, 32 GB of RAM, and running Ubuntu 20.04. We leverage API calls to interact with LLM services. We systematically evaluate CaVulner by addressing the following three research questions (RQs): RQ1. Effectiveness Evaluation. How accurate is CaVulner in identifying vulnerable versions? How does the performance of CaVulner compare to state-of-the-art approaches? RQ2. Ablation Study. What is the contribution of each component of CaVulner to its overall effectiveness? How effective is CaVulner when applied with different LLMs? RQ3. Resource Consumption. What are the costs associated with LLMs?",
